  "prompt": "How can I record video with Drift Ghost-S while charging?",
  "response": "Recording video with your Drift Ghost-S while charging is possible and fairly straightforward. Here's a step-by-step guide on how to do it:\n\n1. **Check Compatibility**: Ensure you have a compatible charging cable and power source. The Drift Ghost-S can be charged via a USB cable connected to a power bank, computer, or wall adapter.\n\n2. **Connect the Cable**: Plug the USB cable into the camera\u2019s USB port. Then, connect the other end to a power source. This can be a power bank for portable charging or a wall adapter for continuous power. \n\n3. **Power On the Camera**: Turn on your Drift Ghost-S camera by pressing the power button.\n\n4. **Start Recording**: Navigate to the recording mode on the camera. You can access this by using the camera's menu system and selecting the video recording option. Press the record button to start recording video.\n\n5. **Confirmation**: Make sure the camera indicates it\u2019s recording (usually via a blinking red light or another indicator on the display).\n\n6. **Battery Icon**: Check the battery icon on the camera\u2019s display to ensure it\u2019s charging. You should see an icon indicating that the camera is receiving power while recording.\n\nBy following these steps, your Drift Ghost-S should be able to record video continuously while being charged. This setup is particularly useful for extended filming sessions where battery life could otherwise be a limiting factor.",
